---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SingleBlog from "../../layouts/SingleBlog.astro";
import CardBlogItem from "../../components/CardBlogItem.astro";
import Icon from "astro-icon";

export function getStaticPaths() {
    return [{ params: { slug: "hello-world" } }];
}

const { slug = "asyo" } = Astro.params;
---

<Layout title={slug}>
    <div
        class="container mx-auto flex flex-col gap-y-12 self-center items-center pt-32 leading-relaxed"
    >
        <!-- Header Content  -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-y-4 w-10/12 lg:w-7/12">
            <!-- title -->
            <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">
                The Powerful Web Framework, AstroJS: Generate Sites with Content
                from Everywhere!
            </h1>
            <p class="text-sm text-grey-200 mb-5">Ahmad Yunus, 12 Juli 2023</p>
            <!-- Hero Image -->
            <div>
                <img src="/image_hero_1.png" class="w-full" />
                <span class="text-sm italic text-center">Image caption</caption>
            </div>
            <hr>
        </div>
        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="tracking-wide w-10/12 lg:w-6/12">
            {slug}
            In today's digital age, having a dynamic and engaging website is essential
            for businesses and individuals alike. With the vast amount of content
            available online, it's crucial to have a web framework that enables you
            to seamlessly integrate and generate content from various sources. That's
            where AstroJS comes in.
            <br />
            <br />
            ## Introducing AstroJS
            <br />
            <br />

            AstroJS is a powerful web framework that revolutionizes the way
            websites are built. It allows developers to generate sites with
            content from everywhere, making it easier than ever to create
            dynamic and interactive web pages. Whether you need to pull content
            from APIs, Markdown files, or even remote websites, AstroJS has got
            you covered.
            <br />
            <br />

            ## The Benefits of AstroJS
            <br />
            <br />

            ### 1. Simplified Content Integration
            <br />
            <br />

            One of the standout features of AstroJS is its ability to seamlessly
            integrate content from various sources. Gone are the days of
            manually copying and pasting content into your website. With
            AstroJS, you can effortlessly pull content from APIs or external
            sources, ensuring that your site is always up to date and dynamic.
            <br />
            <br />

            ### 2. Enhanced Performance
            <br />
            <br />

            AstroJS takes performance seriously. It employs a build-time
            rendering approach, which means that your site is pre-rendered and
            optimized before being deployed. This approach eliminates the need
            for client-side rendering, resulting in faster load times and
            improved overall performance. Your visitors will appreciate the
            snappy and responsive experience AstroJS provides.
            <br />
            <br />

            ### 3. Flexibility and Customization
            <br />
            <br />

            AstroJS offers a wide range of customization options to suit your
            specific needs. It supports various rendering engines, including
            React, Vue.js, and Svelte, allowing you to choose the framework that
            works best for your project. Additionally, AstroJS provides a
            flexible architecture that enables you to build custom components
            and extend functionality effortlessly.
            <br />
            <br />

            ### 4. SEO-Friendly Approach
            <br />
            <br />

            Search engine optimization (SEO) is a crucial aspect of any
            website's success. AstroJS recognizes this and provides built-in SEO
            capabilities. By generating static HTML pages at build time, AstroJS
            ensures that search engines can easily crawl and index your content.
            This improves your site's visibility and helps drive organic traffic
            to your web pages.
            <br />
            <br />

            ### 5. Seamless Collaboration
            <br />
            <br />

            AstroJS promotes seamless collaboration between developers,
            designers, and content creators. Its component-based approach allows
            for modular development, enabling different team members to work on
            specific sections of the website without stepping on each other's
            toes. This streamlines the development process and fosters efficient
            teamwork.
            <br />
            <br />

            ## Conclusion
            <br />
            <br />

            AstroJS is a game-changing web framework that empowers developers to
            generate sites with content from everywhere. Its ability to
            seamlessly integrate content from APIs, Markdown files, and remote
            websites sets it apart from traditional approaches. With AstroJS,
            you can create highly performant, customizable, and SEO-friendly
            websites while enjoying a collaborative development process. Embrace
            the power of AstroJS and take your web development projects to new
            heights!
            <br />
            <br />

            So, what are you waiting for? Give AstroJS a try and unlock the full
            potential of your website-building endeavors!
            <br />
            <br />

            *[APIs]: Application Programming Interfaces *[SEO]: Search Engine
            Optimization
        </div>
        <!-- Share -->

        <!-- Another Blogs -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-y-6 w-10/12 lg:w-7/12">
            <hr>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-y-2 divider divider-y">
                <h1 class="text-orange-500 font-bold text-2xl">More content</h1>
            </div>

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-y-12">
                <CardBlogItem />
                <CardBlogItem />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
